The paper discusses privacy risks in mobile dating apps, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves the use of forensic techniques to analyze data from mobile devices, which could be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) or databases (cs.DB). The paper also touches on the social implications of these apps, which could be classified under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for cyber attacks and data breaches, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY).
